OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,FHousehold energy prices are falling by
OL,7,F7% from Wednesday in a "short-lived
OL,8,Frespite" for households already braced
OL,9,Ffor a predicted 18% hike from July.
OL,11,FOfgem's price cap has dropped from
OL,12,F#1,758 to #1,641 ` a reduction of #117
OL,13,For around #10 a month for the average
OL,14,Fhousehold using both electricity and
OL,15,Fgas.
OL,17,FThis is an 11% fall year on year, but
OL,18,Fstill #600 more than bills were in the
OL,19,Fwinter of 2020 to 2021.
OL,26,@oD@XOUpD@HO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,FThe reduction is lower than the
OL,7,Faverage #150 cut to bills pledged by
OL,8,Fthe Chancellor in November, when she
OL,9,Fmoved 75% of the cost of the
OL,10,Frenewables obligation from household
OL,11,Fbills onto general taxation and
OL,12,Fscrapped the energy company obligation
OL,13,F(Eco) scheme.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,FAnd it comes amid increasing concern
OL,7,Fabout the amount energy bills could
OL,8,Frise by from July as a result of the
OL,9,FMiddle East conflict, with latest
OL,10,Fpredictions from Cornwall Insight
OL,11,Fsuggesting this could be 18% or #288 a
OL,12,Fyear ` to almost #900 above pre-crisis
OL,13,Flevels.
OL,15,FIn the meantime, consumer groups have
OL,16,Furged households to send in meter
OL,17,Freadings to ensure their energy usage
OL,18,Fis billed at the lowest possible rate,
OL,19,Fand investigate fixed rate deals if
OL,20,Fthey remain on their firm's standard
OL,21,Fvariable rate.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,FA spokesman for Energy UK, which
OL,7,Frepresents firms, said: "Suppliers are
OL,8,Frequired to set direct debits as
OL,9,Faccurately as possible based on the
OL,10,Fbest and most current information
OL,11,Favailable.
OL,13,F"So ` as well as factors like current
OL,14,Fbalance, payment record and previous
OL,15,Fenergy usage ` this will also include
OL,16,Fthe latest projection of energy costs
OL,17,Fover the coming months.
OL,26,@oD@YOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"Suppliers regularly review direct
OL,7,Fdebt levels so any current assessment
OL,8,Ffor price cap customers would likely
OL,9,Ftake into account that bills look set
OL,10,Fto go up again in July. Customers on
OL,11,Ffixed deals however will not see any
OL,12,Fincrease until their current deal
OL,13,Fcomes to an end."
OL,15,FSimon Francis, coordinator of the End
OL,16,FFuel Poverty Coalition, said: "The
OL,17,Ffall in bills from April 1 offers
OL,18,Fbrief relief for households, but the
OL,19,Frespite will be short-lived.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@QO]xD@_OU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"Given the ongoing profits made by the
OL,7,Fenergy industry, households deserve
OL,8,Fmore than a temporary reprieve before
OL,9,Fprices rise again.
OL,11,F"For the millions of households
OL,12,Falready in energy debt to their
OL,13,Fsuppliers, this is a real concern and
OL,14,Frisks pushing more people into crisis.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"The Government must use the window
OL,7,Fbetween now and July to act. That
OL,8,Fmeans targeted support for those hit
OL,9,Ffirst and hardest, including
OL,10,Fhouseholds off the gas grid and those
OL,11,Fon heat networks, faster action on
OL,12,Fenergy debt, and preparations to bring
OL,13,Fcosts down if prices deteriorate
OL,14,Ffurther."
OL,16,FNational Energy Action chief executive
OL,17,FAdam Scorer said: "Any price drop is
OL,18,Fgood news, but everyone knows that it
OL,19,Fwill be overtaken by events.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@IO]yD@SOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"It is likely to be a false dawn. And
OL,7,Fthe people who know that the best are
OL,8,Fthose already struggling to afford
OL,9,Ftheir energy bills and know the real
OL,10,Fcost of an energy crisis.
OL,12,F"Unfortunately, today's good news is
OL,13,Fhugely overshadowed by the fear and
OL,14,Fdread of what may be to come."
OL,16,FWhich? energy editor Emily Seymour
OL,17,Fsaid: "April's energy price cap fall
OL,18,Fwill bring much needed relief for
OL,19,Fhouseholds. What you save will vary
OL,20,Fdepending on how much you use.
OL,26,@nD@AOUtD@AOUvD@^O]yD@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"Despite this drop, many households
OL,7,Fare already concerned about the next
OL,8,Fprice cap announcement in May, which
OL,9,Fwill set rates from July and is
OL,10,Fcurrently predicted to rise by #288,
OL,11,For 18%, per year for the average
OL,12,Fhousehold.
OL,14,F"It's important to remember this isn't
OL,15,Fconfirmed yet, so don't feel pressured
OL,16,Finto making quick decisions.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"If you're currently paying variable
OL,7,Frates, it's worth checking the market
OL,8,Fto see what fixed deals are available.
OL,9,FFixing could offer protection against
OL,10,Ffuture increases, but only if the
OL,11,Fprice is right.
OL,13,F"Options have reduced in the last few
OL,14,Fweeks, but some energy companies are
OL,15,Fstill offering fixes with prices
OL,16,Faround those of the January-March
OL,17,Fprice cap.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1775009000
OL,3,CHousehold energy bill drop 'short-
OL,4,Clived respite' amid fears of July hike
OL,6,F"If you're worried about paying your
OL,7,Fenergy bills, contact your supplier as
OL,8,Fsoon as possible. Energy companies are
OL,9,Fobliged to help if you're struggling
OL,10,Fto pay and won't disconnect you for
OL,11,Fmissing a payment. Request a review or
OL,12,Fbreak in payments, and access any
OL,13,Favailable hardship funds."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@ZO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G11/11
